{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ApplicationRef","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" is the foundation of an application. It wraps some"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"low-level platform-specific services and is intended to act as the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"foundation for higher-level application classes such as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"GtkApplication","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MxApplication"},{"text":". In general, you should not use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this class outside of a higher level framework.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" provides convenient life-cycle management by maintaining"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a “use count” for the primary application instance. The use count can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be changed using [method","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.Application.hold","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.Application.release","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]. If it drops to zero, the application","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"exits. Higher-level classes such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkApplication"},{"text":" employ the use count","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to ensure that the application stays alive as long as it has any opened","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"windows.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Another feature that "},{"code":"GApplication","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (optionally) provides is process"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"uniqueness. Applications can make use of this functionality by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"providing a unique application ID. If given, only one application","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with this ID can be running at a time per session. The session"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"concept is platform-dependent, but corresponds roughly to a graphical","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"desktop login. When your application is launched again, its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"arguments are passed through platform communication to the already","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"running program. The already running instance of the program is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"called the “primary instance”; for non-unique applications this is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"always the current instance. On Linux, the D-Bus session bus","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is used for communication.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The use of "},{"code":"GApplication","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" differs from some other commonly-used","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"uniqueness libraries (such as libunique) in important ways. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application is not expected to manually register itself and check"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"if it is the primary instance. Instead, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"main()"},{"type":"text","text":" function of a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"text":" should do very little more than instantiating the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application instance, possibly connecting signal handlers, then"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calling [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Application.run"},{"type":"text","text":"]. All checks for uniqueness are done"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"internally. If the application is the primary instance then the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"startup signal is emitted and the mainloop runs. If the application"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is not the primary instance then a signal is sent to the primary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instance and [method"},{"code":"Gio.Application.run","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] promptly returns. See the code"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"examples below.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If used, the expected form of an application identifier is the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"same as that of a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/dbus.freedesktop.org\/doc\/dbus-specification.html#message-protocol-names-bus"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Examples include: "},{"code":"com.example.MyApp","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"org.example.internal_apps.Calculator"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"org._7_zip.Archiver","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For details on valid application identifiers, see [func"},{"code":"Gio.Application.id_is_valid","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Linux, the application identifier is claimed as a well-known bus name"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the user’s session bus. This means that the uniqueness of your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application is scoped to the current session. It also means that your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application may provide additional services (through registration of other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"object paths) at that bus name. The registration of these object paths","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"should be done with the shared GDBus session bus. Note that due to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"internal architecture of GDBus, method calls can be dispatched at any time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(even if a main loop is not running). For this reason, you must ensure that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"any object paths that you wish to register are registered before "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Application","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"attempts to acquire the bus name of your application (which happens in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Application.register"},{"text":"]). Unfortunately, this means that you cannot","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"use [property","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Application","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] to decide if you want to register"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object paths."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"GApplication","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" also implements the [iface"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroup"},{"type":"text","text":"] and [iface"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionMap","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interfaces and lets you easily export actions by adding them with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"Gio.ActionMap.add_action","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]. When invoking an action by calling"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.ActionGroup.activate_action","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] on the application, it is always"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"invoked in the primary instance. The actions are also exported on"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the session bus, and GIO provides the [class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusActionGroup"},{"type":"text","text":"] wrapper to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conveniently access them remotely. GIO provides a [class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusMenuModel","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"] wrapper","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for remote access to exported [class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModel"},{"type":"text","text":"]s."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note: Due to the fact that actions are exported on the session bus,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"maybe"},{"text":" parameters is not supported, since D-Bus does not support","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"maybe"},{"type":"text","text":" types."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is a number of different entry points into a "},{"code":"GApplication","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"via ‘Activate’ (i.e. just starting the application)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"via ‘Open’ (i.e. opening some files)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"by handling a command-line","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"via activating an action"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The [signal[Application](\/\/documentation\/gio\/application\/onstartup(flags:handler:)] signal lets you handle the application"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"initialization for all of these in a single place."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Regardless of which of these entry points is used to start the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"application, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"text":" passes some ‘platform data’ from the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"launching instance to the primary instance, in the form of a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[struct[Variant](\/\/documentation\/glib\/variant] dictionary mapping strings to variants. To use platform","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"data, override the [vfunc","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.Application.before_emit","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[vfunc"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Application.after_emit"},{"type":"text","text":"] virtual functions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"in your ","type":"text"},{"code":"GApplication","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" subclass. When dealing with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[class","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationCommandLine"},{"type":"text","text":"] objects, the platform data is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directly available via [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ApplicationCommandLine.get_cwd"},{"type":"text","text":"],"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"Gio.ApplicationCommandLine.get_environ","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ApplicationCommandLine.get_platform_data"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As the name indicates, the platform data may vary depending on the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operating system, but it always includes the current directory (key"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"cwd","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"), and optionally the environment (ie the set of environment","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"variables and their values) of the calling process (key ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"environ"},{"type":"text","text":")."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The environment is only added to the platform data if the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_APPLICATION_SEND_ENVIRONMENT","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flag is set. ","type":"text"},{"code":"GApplication","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" subclasses","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can add their own platform data by overriding the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[vfunc"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Application.add_platform_data"},{"type":"text","text":"] virtual function. For instance,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" adds startup notification data in this way."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To parse commandline arguments you may handle the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[signal[Application](\/\/documentation\/gio\/application\/oncommandline(flags:handler:)] signal or override the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[vfunc","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Application.local_command_line"},{"type":"text","text":"] virtual function, to parse them in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"either the primary instance or the local instance, respectively."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For an example of opening files with a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"text":", see","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/gitlab.gnome.org\/GNOME\/glib\/-\/blob\/HEAD\/gio\/tests\/gapplication-example-open.c"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For an example of using actions with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"text":", see","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/gitlab.gnome.org\/GNOME\/glib\/-\/blob\/HEAD\/gio\/tests\/gapplication-example-actions.c"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For an example of using extra D-Bus hooks with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"type":"text","text":", see"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/gitlab.gnome.org\/GNOME\/glib\/-\/blob\/HEAD\/gio\/tests\/gapplication-example-dbushooks.c","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" only as an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference to an existing ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Application","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef"},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" is the core class for application support."}],"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ApplicationRef","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"ApplicationRef","externalID":"s:3GIO14ApplicationRefV","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ApplicationRef","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"struct","roleHeading":"Structure","role":"symbol"},"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupProtocol","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionMapProtocol","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol","doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GIO\/10GLibObject14GWeakCapturingP","doc:\/\/GIO\/10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP"],"type":"conformsTo"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/init(_:)-49ry0","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/init(_:)-4bqmn","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/init(_:)-55772","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/init(_:)-5ckzj","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/init(_:)-8dapr","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/init(applicationID:flags:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers"},{"title":"Instance Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/ptr"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"generated":true,"title":"Type Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/getDefault()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/unowned(_:)"],"anchor":"Type-Methods"},{"title":"Default Implementations","anchor":"Default-Implementations","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/ActionGroupProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/ActionMapProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/ApplicationProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/GWeakCapturing-Implementations","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations"]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/applicationref"]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationRef":{"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ApplicationRef","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/applicationref","title":"ApplicationRef","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ApplicationRef"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"text":" is the core class for application support.","type":"text"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationProtocol/application_ptr-1p34t":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol\/application_ptr-1p34t","required":true,"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"application_ptr","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"GApplication","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">!"}],"defaultImplementations":1,"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/applicationprotocol\/application_ptr-1p34t","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Typed pointer to the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"role":"symbol","title":"application_ptr"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ActionGroup":{"role":"symbol","title":"ActionGroup","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ActionGroup"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroup","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ActionGroup","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/actiongroup","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GActionGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" represents a group of actions."}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Application":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Application"}],"title":"Application","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" is the core class for application support."}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Application","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Application","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/application"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationCommandLine":{"title":"ApplicationCommandLine","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ApplicationCommandLine","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ApplicationCommandLine"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/applicationcommandline","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationCommandLine","abstract":[{"code":"GApplicationCommandLine","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" represents a command-line invocation of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"an application.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/4GLib14PointerWrapperP":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","title":"GLib.PointerWrapper","type":"unresolvable"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationRef/getDefault()":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the default "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Application"},{"text":" instance for this process.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"getDefault","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ApplicationRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14ApplicationRefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"title":"getDefault()","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/getDefault()","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/applicationref\/getdefault()","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationRef/init(_:)-8dapr":{"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/applicationref\/init(_:)-8dapr","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"GApplication","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">)"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationRef\/init(_:)-8dapr","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Designated initialiser from a constant pointer to the underlying "},{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" data type","type":"text"}],"title":"init(_:)","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DBusMenuModel":{"title":"DBusMenuModel","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DBusMenuModel","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DBusMenuModel","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDBusMenuModel"},{"type":"text","text":" is an implementation of [class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModel","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] that can be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"used as a proxy for a menu model that is exported over D-Bus with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"Gio.DBusConnection.export_menu_model","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/dbusmenumodel","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusMenuModel","role":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationRef/init(_:)-4bqmn":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Designated initialiser from the underlying "},{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"}